The paper deals with graph theory and computational complexity, which are topics that are commonly found in the arXiv categories of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Graph Theory (cs.GT), and Computational Complexity (cs.CC). The paper's focus on the computational complexity of a graph problem suggests that cs.CC is the most likely category. The paper's use of graph classes and algorithms to solve the problem suggests that cs.DM and cs.DS are also likely categories. The paper's use of planar graphs and chordal graphs suggests that cs.CG and cs.GT are also possible categories.
